        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add session-limit reset confetti celebration",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds an opt-in **Session limit confetti** celebration that plays full-screen confetti when a provider's **session** usage resets — mirroring the existing weekly-limit celebration.\n\nUnder the hood, the weekly-limit reset detector is generalized into a shared limit-reset detector so both the session and weekly plan-utilization series are tracked by the same code path, with separate persisted state per series.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **Detector refactor** (`UsageStore+PlanUtilization.swift`): rename `WeeklyLimitResetDetectorState` → `LimitResetDetectorState`; `postWeeklyLimitResetCelebrationIfNeeded` now drives a shared `postLimitResetCelebrationIfNeeded` for both `.session` and `.weekly`, with load/persist parameterized by defaults key + series name. Account identifier/label helpers renamed `weeklyLimitReset*` → `limitReset*`.\n- **Event/notification** (`Notifications+CodexBar.swift`, `UsageStore.swift`): new `codexbarSessionLimitReset` notification + `SessionLimitResetEvent`, with a dedicated `sessionLimitResetDetectorStates` store loaded at init.\n- **Setting** (`SettingsStore*.swift`): `confettiOnSessionLimitResetsEnabled` (default **off**) wired through defaults, state, and menu observation.\n- **App wiring** (`CodexbarApp.swift`): new observer plus a shared `playLimitResetConfetti(provider:accountIdentifier:resetKind:)` used by both session and weekly handlers.\n- **UI + i18n**: new toggle in the Advanced pane; `session_limit_confetti_title/subtitle` localized across all supported languages.\n- **Tests**: session reset detection and the new setting are covered (`UsageStorePlanUtilizationTests`, `SettingsStoreTests`).\n- **Changelog**: entry added under `0.37.4 — Unreleased`.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `swift build` — succeeds\n- `swift test --filter CodexBarTests.UsageStorePlanUtilizationTests` — 42 tests pass\n- `swift test --filter CodexBarTests.SettingsStoreTests` — 58 tests pass\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\n",
